description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We have a newly created opportunity to employ a full time (37.5 hours), Community Healthcare Assistant on a 1 year fixed term contract to support our existing Community Nursing Teams at Wymondham, Attleborough, Long Stratton, Loddon and Diss. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will work across the above listed sites to support the existing Community Nursing Teams and will become a valuable team member whilst being able to develop their own skills.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We see people in their own homes (own transport will be required) for a variety of interventions, including diabetes care / insulin administration, wound care, venepuncture, and catheter care. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our service works 7 days a week. You will be able to demonstrate flexibility as well a sound clinical basis and understanding of community working. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We would welcome prospective applicants to contact us for further information and to have an informal discussion.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews have been provisionally booked to run on 26/11/20.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Apply now to join an organisation that has been awarded an ‘Outstanding’ rating by the Care Quality Commission (CQC), the highest possible rating and the first stand-alone NHS community trust in the country to be awarded the title.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Philip Squire&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Clinical Operations Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address philip.squire@nchc.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 07795014179&lt;/p&gt;
